reviews.text: Station fine, car park an absolute rip off. Was charged £13 for the priveledge of overnight parking 6:00pm ish to 07:30am, absolutely outrageous.
Nice little station, convenient for me.

A brilliant attraction that changes its theme throughout the seasons. Lots of crafts and activities for children to get involved in and plenty of space to enjoy a picnic with the family. The estate also has a significant residence on the opposite side of the road so you are able to visit the house for a bit of culture. Best not to do this with younger children however.

Nice clean station, with very helpful staff, lift to platform. Small shop for coffee/tea papers etc its has good selection of wine and local florist 'Bluebells and Brambles' has a flower stall Friday nights which is very handy.

Nice little station with taxi rank and bus stop. Ticket office is manned, there is a small newsagents as part of the station and free toilets.  There is no ticket barrier and there is a collection ticket machine on the platform.
